Theory of Lovasz extension The Lovasz extension is proposed to form an interpolating function for a sub-modular set function. In this article, we are discussing about the theory and the results from this paper: &ldquo;The Lovász-Softmax loss: A tractable surrogate for the optimization of the intersection-over-union measure in neural networks&rdquo;,
Reference
To get more details, we have the further reading material about Lovasz-hinge optimization: &ldquo;The Lovász Hinge: A Novel Convex Surrogate for Submodular Losses&ldquo;
